- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a deep representation learning framework for encoding evolving information over dynamic graphs into low-dimensional representations. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper deals with dynamic graphs and focuses on the communication and association between nodes in these graphs. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering): Although not the main focus, the paper discusses an efficient unsupervised learning procedure, which could be of interest to the software engineering community. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a novel approach for dynamic link prediction and event time prediction, which could be of interest to the AI community. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper deals with the problem of encoding evolving information over dynamic graphs, which involves designing efficient algorithms and data structures.
